        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 12:51AM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 1250 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Gleason, or 9 miles west of McKenzie, moving northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sandhill, Tuckers Corner, Mansfield, Dresden, Bradford, Good Luck,
Cottage Grove, Como, Staffords Store, Whitlock, Vaughns Grove, Porter
Court, McKenzie, Routon, Henry, Ore Springs, Greenfield, Skullbone,
Gleason, and Hinkledale.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
